# AZ-104 Lab 02a - Manage Subscriptions and RBAC

## Overview
This lab demonstrates how to manage Azure subscriptions using Management Groups and Azure Role-Based Access Control (RBAC).

---

## Task 1: Implement Management Groups
- Created a Management Group named **az104-mg1**.
- Verified the Management Group hierarchy in the Azure portal.

![Task 1 - Management Group](screenshots/Task-1-Management-Group.png)

---

## Task 2: Assign a Built-in RBAC Role
- Assigned the **Virtual Machine Contributor** role to the **Helpdesk** group.
- Verified the role assignment in **Access Control (IAM)**.

![Task 2 - Role Assignment](screenshots/Task-2-Role-Assignment.png)

---

## Task 3: Create a Custom RBAC Role
- Created a custom role named **Custom Support Request**.
- Cloned the **Support Request Contributor** role.
- Excluded the **Microsoft.Support/Register** permission.
- Assigned the role to the Management Group.

![Task 3 - Custom Role](screenshots/Task-3-Custom-Role.png)

---

## Task 4: Monitor Role Assignments
- Reviewed the **Azure Activity Log**.
- Verified role assignment and management activities.

![Task 4 - Activity Log](screenshots/Task-4-Activity-Log.png)

